# Animica Contracts — Environment Example
# ---------------------------------------
# Copy this file to ".env" in the same directory and fill in the values below.
# The Makefile and helper scripts will read these variables to:
#  • talk to your node's JSON-RPC endpoint
#  • target the correct chain/network id
#  • (optionally) request test funds from a faucet
#  • derive a deployer keypair from a mnemonic for signing
#
# Usage:
#   cp contracts/.env.example contracts/.env
#   # edit contracts/.env
#   # then either:
#   set -a; source contracts/.env; set +a
#   make -C contracts build
#
# Security:
#   • NEVER commit your real mnemonic to source control.
#   • Keep contracts/.env out of VCS (add to .gitignore).
#   • Use distinct mnemonics per network (dev/test/prod).

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RPC_URL — HTTP(S) URL to the node's JSON-RPC endpoint.
# The Animica RPC mounts JSON-RPC at /rpc and WebSocket at /ws.
# Examples:
#   http://127.0.0.1:8645/rpc          (local devnet)
#   https://rpc.dev.animica.org/rpc    (hosted devnet)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
RPC_URL="http://127.0.0.1:8645/rpc"

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CHAIN_ID — numeric chain id you are targeting.
# Per spec/chains.json (CAIP-2 registry):
#   1     = mainnet
#   2     = testnet
#   1337  = devnet (default for local testing)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CHAIN_ID="1337"

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FAUCET — Optional faucet endpoint for requesting test funds.
# Leave as "disabled" to skip. If set to a URL, the tools will POST there.
# Example studio-services faucet endpoint:
#   http://127.0.0.1:8787/faucet/drip
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FAUCET="disabled"
# FAUCET="http://127.0.0.1:8787/faucet/drip"

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DEPLOYER_MNEMONIC — 12/24-word mnemonic used to derive the deployer account.
# This is consumed by the Python SDK signer (Deterministic PQ keys).
# For CI/devnet, you can use a throwaway mnemonic. For production, use a secure
# secret manager instead of a plaintext .env file.
# Example (DO NOT USE IN PRODUCTION):
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DEPLOYER_MNEMONIC="abandon abandon abandon abandon abandon abandon abandon abandon abandon abandon abandon about"

# Notes:
# • The default PQ signing algorithm is configured by the SDK/wallet; this .env
#   only supplies the seed material (mnemonic). If you need to override alg_id,
#   do so in the tool invocations or SDK config (not here).
# • If your node is behind a reverse proxy, ensure /rpc is forwarded verbatim and
#   CORS allows your origin when using browser flows.
